						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar set up outside the Madanagōpālasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in Śaka 1220, <hi rend="italic">Pushya</hi> ba. 7, Thursday, uttarāyaṇa-sankrānti. May correspond to A.D., 1298, December 25.</p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 50 buffaloes for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mārkaṇḍēśvara at Rājamahēndrapura by Pōta-sāni, daughter of Pōtakaṟēni (Cf. No. 246- A.R. No. 8 of 1956-57) and wife of Malli-nēḍu for her own merit. The buffaloes were entrusted to Prōle-bōya, son of Malle-bōya.</p>						

						</summary>
